<title type="html"><![CDATA[Anime/Manga]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5898&amp;p=54657#p54657"><![CDATA[
I don't usually discuss anime/manga much, but if I want to talk about a specific series I go to places that are specific to that series, I don't go to a generic place where all series are welcome, so I can't recommend anything.<br /><br />About drawing, I learned mostly from copying at first, and once I had done enough copying I had learned the basic "rules" and was able to come up with my own stuff. I guess you should pay attention to the different styles and try to replicate some of them, but in the end you shouldn't rely on memory or formulas to draw, or your drawings will be very repetitive. Hopefully you will learn how to draw instead of memorizing how things should be drawn.<br /><br />I started 15 years ago though (I did draw before that, but that was when I switched to manga style), so it's not a very quick thing to learn, specially if you aren't used to drawing at all.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jan 03, 2010 1:58 pm</p><hr />
